my own selfie.

00:08:42.820 --> 00:08:44.920
So that's my thing.

00:08:44.920 --> 00:08:47.470
And what you see in the
years-- in these years,

00:08:47.470 --> 00:08:50.640
this period of 2008
to 2012, really--

00:08:50.640 --> 00:08:55.570
is a community of
extremely passionate people

00:08:55.570 --> 00:08:59.650
coalesce around a currency,
which is a really odd thing.

00:08:59.650 --> 00:09:02.080
I mean, to think of a
counterculture movement born

00:09:02.080 --> 00:09:05.120
around a coin, even
a digital coin,

00:09:05.120 --> 00:09:06.660
it doesn't usually happen.

00:09:06.660 --> 00:09:09.850
But this community
grows, and it's techies.

00:09:09.850 --> 00:09:11.350
It's libertarians.

00:09:11.350 --> 00:09:17.370
It's people who are just kind
of fed up with the system.

00:09:17.370 --> 00:09:20.210
And it becomes a
cultural movement.

00:09:20.210 --> 00:09:21.690
It was really interesting.

00:09:21.690 --> 00:09:24.780
And what you start to see is--
and I'm going to pull up here.

00:09:24.780 --> 00:09:27.900
This is some artwork by
