00:58:28.590 --> 00:58:31.175
say it could stay
as middle aged,

00:58:31.175 --> 00:58:34.200
or become young again, from its
senior citizen status in terms

00:58:34.200 --> 00:58:34.950
of network awards?

00:58:34.950 --> 00:58:37.830
PAUL VIGNA: Well, again,
I think that's an issue,

00:58:37.830 --> 00:58:41.510
especially if you
have invested hundreds

00:58:41.510 --> 00:58:44.050
of thousands or millions of
dollars in infrastructure

00:58:44.050 --> 00:58:47.920
to be the person, to be
the miner, to be the node.

00:58:47.920 --> 00:58:49.370
The price matters a lot.

00:58:49.370 --> 00:58:50.360
The fees matter a lot.

00:58:50.360 --> 00:58:50.860
Right?

00:58:50.860 --> 00:58:53.370
It kind of gets back to
what you were saying.

00:58:53.370 --> 00:58:56.600
Idealistically, this would
not be good for Bitcoin.

00:58:56.600 --> 00:58:59.490
But I would love to see the
price go down to like $30

00:58:59.490 --> 00:59:02.480
and see what happens there,
see the shake out there.

00:59:02.480 --> 00:59:04.100
And then you would
have a situation

00:59:04.100 --> 00:59:06.100
where it would be cheap
